573
00:39:12,145 --> 00:39:14,505
-Happy birthday to you
-Happy birthday to you

574
00:39:16,065 --> 00:39:17,225
-Make a wish!
-Make a wish!

575
00:39:17,305 --> 00:39:18,145
Hurry!

576
00:39:20,465 --> 00:39:21,385
Can I say it out loud?

577
00:39:21,465 --> 00:39:22,745
-No.
-No.

578
00:39:22,825 --> 00:39:23,985
Blow out the candle.

579
00:39:26,265 --> 00:39:27,625
Happy birthday!

580
00:39:27,705 --> 00:39:29,865
-You're another year older now.
-Put it down.

581
00:39:31,065 --> 00:39:32,585
Why do you have two cakes?

582
00:39:33,505 --> 00:39:35,945
This one looks terrible!

583
00:39:36,025 --> 00:39:36,865
No, it's not.

584
00:39:36,945 --> 00:39:38,345
I think it looks adorable.

585
00:39:40,145 --> 00:39:41,665
Don't tell me

586
00:39:41,745 --> 00:39:43,385
that your crush made it for you.

587
00:39:44,905 --> 00:39:46,025
Is it that obvious?

588
00:39:46,105 --> 00:39:47,545
Really?

589
00:39:48,505 --> 00:39:50,465
Did your date go well today?

590
00:39:51,665 --> 00:39:52,705
Tell us about it.

591
00:39:53,825 --> 00:39:55,105
I did have a good time.

592
00:39:56,145 --> 00:39:57,185
If so,

593
00:39:57,265 --> 00:39:59,105
was there any substantial progress?

594
00:40:01,785 --> 00:40:02,705
Yes.

595
00:40:04,025 --> 00:40:05,785
I knew it!

596
00:40:05,865 --> 00:40:07,545
-Tell us!
-Spill it!

597
00:40:07,625 --> 00:40:08,465
-Hurry.
-Tell us.

598
00:40:08,545 --> 00:40:09,425
I…

599
00:40:10,025 --> 00:40:10,865
What is it?

600
00:40:11,505 --> 00:40:12,705
I think you guys understand.

601
00:40:16,225 --> 00:40:17,545
I can't take it anymore. Come on.

602
00:40:17,625 --> 00:40:18,625
He's so good at this.

603
00:40:41,545 --> 00:40:42,865
Put your back into it.

604
00:40:42,945 --> 00:40:44,185
Knead it repeatedly.

605
00:40:44,265 --> 00:40:46,465
Yes, knead it into the shape of a circle,

606
00:40:46,545 --> 00:40:47,665
then roll it out.

607
00:40:53,065 --> 00:40:53,945
No, not like that.

608
00:40:54,025 --> 00:40:55,625
Here, let me show you.

609
00:40:55,705 --> 00:40:57,145
Roll it out forward.

610
00:40:57,905 --> 00:40:59,105
When you're almost to the end,

611
00:40:59,185 --> 00:41:00,185
you have to roll it back.

612
00:41:00,265 --> 00:41:01,825
You can't just roll in one direction.

613
00:41:01,905 --> 00:41:03,225
-Got it?
-Okay, let me try.

614
00:41:08,105 --> 00:41:09,545
You refused to learn this

615
00:41:09,625 --> 00:41:10,785
when you worked at my shop

616
00:41:11,385 --> 00:41:12,505
when you were in 12th grade.

617
00:41:12,585 --> 00:41:14,425
Now you're suddenly back to learn it.

618
00:41:14,985 --> 00:41:16,225
Are you seeing someone?

619
00:41:19,985 --> 00:41:20,945
Am I right?

620
00:41:23,505 --> 00:41:24,545
You brat.

621
00:41:26,465 --> 00:41:27,345
Listen.

622
00:41:28,145 --> 00:41:29,545
A cake that you put your heart into

623
00:41:29,625 --> 00:41:30,905
will taste different.

624
00:41:32,465 --> 00:41:33,425
Remember that.

625
00:41:34,105 --> 00:41:35,585
Okay, flatten it out.

626
00:41:36,265 --> 00:41:37,745
That's right. Forward and backward.

627
00:41:37,825 --> 00:41:39,625
Be careful. That's it.

628
00:41:46,665 --> 00:41:48,025
Why is it cracked?

629
00:41:48,585 --> 00:41:49,705
Did I bake it for too long?

630
00:41:50,825 --> 00:41:51,705
Listen.

631
00:41:52,585 --> 00:41:53,545
Don't be discouraged.

632
00:41:53,625 --> 00:41:55,105
It's a tough one to make.

633
00:41:55,185 --> 00:41:56,345
You should've listened to me

634
00:41:56,425 --> 00:41:58,105
and made something simpler.

635
00:41:58,185 --> 00:42:00,065
It's fine. I'll try again.
